suburb east of Polokwane in February .Police spokesperson Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo, said the businessman
was identified as Ngwako William Mathebula - who was the owner of Thaba
Security Company.Mojapelo says the incident began with Mathebula's 11-year-old
son being confronted by three unknown suspects at his home's gate.The attackers then pushed the child back into the yard,
together with the house-keeper and later on shot him dead.Mojapelo said a team of Polokwane detectives who were
assisted by the Provincial Tracking Team arrested a highly wanted suspect in
Lephalale, who was allegedly involved in the killing of Mathebula. He said the information on his arrest was restricted to
enable the operatives to make a follow-up on other crucial information that led
to the arrest of the alleged girlfriend.The police recovered one firearm, ten live rounds of
ammunition and two cars during this operation.Provincial Commissioner Lieutenant General Nneke Ledwaba commended
the members that were involved in the breakthrough.The police also made the call for Victor Mashakeng to avail
himself to the police, Cops say it is
